!iflang [english]

!begin_node  List boxes

The following routines were introduced with MagiC 4, and permit the
creation and hadling of list boxes:

!begin_xlist [x lbox_get_slct_item] !compressed
!item [(!bullet) lbox_ascroll_to]
Positions slider A of the list box
!item [(!bullet) lbox_bscroll_to]
 Positions slider B of the list box
!item [(!bullet) lbox_cnt_items]
Obtains number of list items
!item [(!bullet) lbox_create]
Creates a list box
!item [(!bullet) lbox_delete]
Releases memory allocated for a list box
!item [(!bullet) lbox_do]
Processes button of a list box
!item [(!bullet) lbox_free_items]
Releases items list
!item [(!bullet) lbox_free_list]
Releases items list
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_afirst]
Obtains index of first visible item (slider A)
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_avisb]
Obtains number of visible entries (slider A)
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_bentries]
Obtains number of entries (slider B)
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_bfirst]
Obtains index of first visible item (slider B)
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_bvis]
Obtains number of visible entries (slider B)
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_idx]
Obtains index of an item
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_item]
Returns pointer to n-th item
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_items]
Returns pointer to the first item
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_slct_idx]
Obtains index of the first selected item
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_slct_item]
Returns pointer to the first selected item
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_tree]
Obtains object tree of the dialog
!item [(!bullet) lbox_get_udata]
Gets pointer to program-specific data
!item [(!bullet) lbox_set_asldr]
Sets position of the slider A
!item [(!bullet) lbox_set_bentries]
Sets number of entries for slider B
!item [(!bullet) lbox_set_bsldr]
Sets position of the slider B
!item [(!bullet) lbox_set_items]
Sets new items list
!item [(!bullet) lbox_update]
Updates list box
!end_xlist

(!B)Hint:(!b)
The presence of this call should be checked for using
(!link [appl_getinfo][%apgi_7]) (Opcode 7).

See also: (!nl)
Calling procedure for modal dialogs ~ Style guidelines ~ WDIALOG

